{"first_name":"Kent","last_name":"Fuka","permalink":"kent-fuka-2","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/kent-fuka-2","homepage_url":"http://www.linkedin.com/in/kentfuka","birthplace":"Illinois","twitter_username":"kentfuka","blog_url":"http://thirdipo.typepad.com/3rd_ipo/","blog_feed_url":"http://feeds.feedburner.com/3rdIpo","affiliation_name":"Thinkwell Corporation","born_year":1956,"born_month":12,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"elearning, venture-capital, publishing, consulting","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Fri Oct 26 21:00:54 UTC 2012","updated_at":"Fri Nov 02 07:01:28 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>Kent Fuka is a serial-entrepreneur and a retired venture capitalist.   He was an early employee at three VC-backed startup companies, each of which had successful IPOs.  Kent currently serves as Chairman of the Board of Thinkwell, an eLearning company headquartered in Austin.  Kent also advises several startup teams in Austin and in New Mexico.  Kent has been a board member for a number of startup companies in Texas.  Prior to entering the venture capital business in 1996, Kent was VP of Customer Operations for Tivoli Systems in Austin.  Prior to Tivoli, Kent held a variety of management roles at Convex Computer Corp in Dallas.  Kent began is career in Boston, where we joined his first startup-company, Apollo Computer. Kent has managed software development projects, world-wide customer support teams, and product marketing efforts. Kent also has served as CFO of Thinkwell since 2004.  Kent has an undergraduate degree in Computer Science and a graduate degree in Astronomy.  Kent&#8217;s company, KNCL Management provides strategic services to tech startups.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[107,150],"assets/images/resized/0021/7454/217454v2-max-150x150.jpg"],[[178,250],"assets/images/resized/0021/7454/217454v2-max-250x250.jpg"],[[321,450],"assets/images/resized/0021/7454/217454v2-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":""},"degrees":[{"degree_type":"BS","subject":"Compu